
[1]sherbet

   SHER'BET, n. [L. sorbeo.] A drink composed of water, lemon juice and
   sugar, sometimes with perfumed cakes dissolved in it, with an infusion
   of some drops of rose water. Another kind made with violets, honey,
   juice of rasins, &c.
